---
description: Keep FFTS self-contained and independent of sibling repositories
alwaysApply: true
---

# Workspace Independence

- Do not add runtime, test, script, rule, task, or configuration dependencies on sibling repositories.
- Do not copy credentials, generated auth state, production records, private logs, deployment identifiers, or customer branding from another project.
- Use only repository-relative FFTS paths in executable and configuration files.
- Keep `ffts.code-workspace` limited to the current repository.
- Historical comparison text may remain in documentation, but it must never become an operational dependency.

